items:
  - name: Linear
    summary: |
      Poses interpolate linearly between key frames.
    value: 0
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: ''
  - name: Constant
    summary: |
      Poses do not interpolate but snap to the key frame indicated by the
      Enum.PoseEasingDirection.
    value: 1
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: ''
  - name: Elastic
    summary: |
      Pose interpolation will overshoot like it is elastic.
    value: 2
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: ''
  - name: Cubic
    summary: |
      Deprecated - Use Enum.PoseEasingStyle.CubicV2. Pose interpolation is a
      cubic curve between keyframes based on the Enum.PoseEasingDirection.
    value: 3
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: |
      Use CubicV2 going forward, Cubic has a bug where the direction is reversed
      between the editor and runtime.
  - name: Bounce
    summary: |
      Pose interpolation produces a bounce like effect between key frames.
    value: 4
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: ''
  - name: CubicV2
    summary: |
      Pose interpolation is a cubic curve between keyframes based on
      Enum.PoseEasingDirection.
    value: 5
    tags: []
    deprecationmessage: ''
